IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: SERVE THE PUBLIC BY IMPROVING CARE IN PM&R THROUGH PHYSICIAN CERTIFICATION AND CONTINUOUS CERTIFICATION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF THE AMERICAN BOARD OF PHYSICAL MEDICINE AND REHABILITATION (ABPMR) IS TO SERVE THE PUBLIC BY IMPROVING THE QUALITY OF PATIENT CARE IN PHYSICAL MEDICINE AND REHABILITATION (PM&R). THIS IS ACCOMPLISHED THROUGH A PROCESS OF CERTIFICATION AND CONTINUING CERTIFICATION THAT FOSTERS EXCELLENCE AND ENCOURAGES CONTINUOUS LEARNING.
IRS990.Desc: THE ABPMR SUPPORTS AND SERVES THE PHYSICIANS WHO HAVE GAINED OR ARE WORKING TO ACHIEVE BOARD CERTIFICATION IN PM&R. THIS STARTS BY ENSURING HIGH-QUALITY RESIDENCY TRAINING AND CULMINATES IN A RIGOROUS AND RELIABLE TWO-PART EXAMINATION TO ACHIEVE BOARD CERTIFICATION. ONCE CERTIFIED, A PHYSICIAN IS CALLED A DIPLOMATE OF THE ABPMR.THE ABPMR'S WORK CONTINUES THROUGHOUT A PHYSIATRIST'S CAREER WITH OUR MAINTENANCE OF CERTIFICATION (MOC) PROGRAM, WHICH PROVIDES A FRAMEWORK AND TOOLS FOR MAINTAINING MEDICAL KNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS, AS WELL AS TRACKING CONTINUOUS IMPROVEMENT OVER TIME. THE AMERICAN BOARD OF PHYSICAL MEDICINE AND REHABILITATION (ABPMR) OFFERS CERTIFICATION EXAMINATIONS. THE THREE LARGEST PROGRAM SERVICES OFFERED BY THE ABPMR ARE THE PART I, AND PART II EXAMINATIONS. THE NUMBER OF PERSONS TO BENEFIT FROM THE EXAMS FOR 2022 ARE AS FOLLOWS:PART I - 519PART II - 494

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: IN ADDITION TO OFFERING PRIMARY CERTIFICATION IN PM&R, THE ABPMR ALSO OFFERS SUBSPECIALTY CERTIFICATION IN: COMBINED SUBSPECIALTY EXAMS BENEFITED 669 PERSONS IN 2022.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: THE CONTINUING CERTIFICATION PROGRAM, INCLUDING LONGITUDINAL ASSESSMENT, CME, QUALITY IMPROVEMENT, AND PROFESSIONALISM HAD 9,500 PARTICIPANTS IN 2022.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD IS EXEMPT FROM PAYING INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(6) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND SIMILAR STATE STATUTES. THUS, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES IS INCLUDED IN THE ACCOMPANYING FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE BOARD FOLLOWS THE ACCOUNTING GUIDANCE FOR ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES. THE BOARD IS SUBJECT TO FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES TO THE EXTENT IT HAS UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME. IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE GUIDANCE FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THE BOARD'S MATERIAL TAX POSITIONS AND DETERMINED THAT THERE ARE NO INCOME TAX EFFECTS WITH RESPECT TO ITS FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. GENERALLY, THE BOARD IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS BY THE U.S. FEDERAL, STATE OR LOCAL AUTHORITIES FOR YEARS BEYOND THREE YEARS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ABPMR STAFF COMPLETES THE WORKPAPERS AND QUESTIONNAIRES FOR THE 990 AND PROVIDES THEM TO RSM US LLP. RSM US LLP SENDS THE DRAFT COMPLETED 990 TO ABPMR. APPROPRIATE STAFF REVIEW THE 990 AND MAKES NECESSARY COMMENTS TO RSM US LLP. EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD REVIEWS BEFORE FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: VOLUNTEERS OF THE BOARD ARE REQUIRED TO SIGN APPROPRIATE POLICIES ON CONFIDENTIALITY AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST ANNUALLY. EMPLOYEES ARE REQUIRED TO SIGN AT THE START OF THEIR EMPLOYMENT AND AS NEEDED. ANYTHING NOTED ON THE FORM APPEARING TO BE IN CONFLICT OF INTEREST WILL BE ADDRESSED BY THE BOARD. THE BOARD CHAIR AND/OR EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL, WITH LEGAL COUNSEL AS APPROPRIATE, REVIEW THE DISCLOSURE FORMS AND MAY REQUEST ANY DIRECTOR WITH A CONFLICT TO TAKE THE APPROPRIATE ACTION (EG, DISCLOSURE, REFUSAL, RESIGNATION) IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IF THE DIRECTOR HAS NOT ALREADY INDICATED THAT HE/SHE WILL DO SO.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION OF KEY EMPLOYEE'S IS EVALUATED ANNUALLY TO ENSURE SALARIES ARE IN LINE WITH THE EMPLOYEE'S RESPONSIBILITIES AND THE MARKET BY USING AN EXTERNAL BENCHMARKING COMPANY. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS APPROVES THE SALARIES OF ALL EMPLOYEES. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE VOLUNTEERS AND ARE NOT COMPENSATED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST FOR THE SAME PERIOD OF DISCLOSURE AS SET FORTH IN SECTION 6104(D).

ABPMR HAS AN AUDIT COMMITTEE THAT REVIEWS THE ANNUAL AUDIT. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD (THAT SERVES AS THE FINANCE COMMITTEE) WOULD APPROVE ANY CHANGE TO THE SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT. THERE HAS BEEN NO CHANGE IN THE PROCESS FROM THE PREVIOUS YEAR.
